str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.

str2: (primarily physical), I look, see, perceive, discern. A primary verb; to look at.
A woman, wife, my lady. Probably from the base of ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.
To long for, covet, lust after, set the heart upon. From epi and thumos; to set the heart upon, i.e. Long for.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Already; now at length, now after all this waiting. Apparently from e and de; even now.

str2: To commit adultery (of a man with a married woman, but also of a married man). From moichos; to commit adultery.
